Promised Land, He's Gone, Black Throated Wind, Friend Of The Devil, Jack Straw, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Me & My Uncle, Sugaree, Beat It On Down The Line, Stella Blue, Playin' In The Band, Brown Eyed Women, Mexicali Blues, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, Ramble On Rose, Dark Star-> El Paso-> Jam-> Deal, Sugar Magnolia, Mississippi Half Step, Uncle John's Band-> One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Come on Peeps, This is the Real McCoy This phenomenal, under-rated show, often overlooked by others in this very run or the days away show in Veneta, must be heard.  And its never sounded better than this Miller/SirMick master. The China-Rider is outstanding, the PITB smokes and the Stella is a masterpiece that really does "melt into a dream." O'h and did I mention there's a pretty special Dark Star-El Paso to boot? Yeah, I did. Start to finish, this is a simply a classic, vintage performance by a band hitting full stride and firing on all cylinders.  Major thanks to all involved, and now enjoy a show for the ages!

Underappreciated! I agree with Katfish John -- this is an outstanding show and one I listen to often. I wish they would release the Berkeley shows in a box set (well, maybe I would rather they didn't), definitely a stellar performance during a stellar run/year.
